#week-title("Four", "The Accumulated Vigil & Seasonal Integration")

=== Core Teaching

The deepest revelations of nature occur through *accumulation*. The alchemist
returns to the same plant repeatedly, across different times of day, lunar
phases, and seasons. This "accumulated vigil" allows the persistent, essential
signature of the plant to stand out from the transient accidents of weather or
growth stage.

Seasonal awareness is vital. The way a plant responds to the transition from
summer to autumn, or winter to spring, reveals the underlying cycle of
generation and corruption (the Lesser Circulation) that the Tyro is studying in
the laboratory.

=== Topics This Week

- The accumulated vigil: consistency over time
- Observing the Lesser Circulation in the field
- Integration of field notes with laboratory observations

